    "These findings hold substantial clinical relevance, as anxiety and depressive symptoms are associated with an elevated risk of subsequent cardiac events (Bakker et al. 2021; Celano et al. 2015; Emdin et al. 2016), and exercise-based CR programs have demonstrated their efficacy in reducing levels of anxiety and depression (Korzeniowska-Kubacka et al. 2017; Lavie and Milani 2004).",
    "Additionally, Bakker et al. (2021) identified an association between anxiety in CAD patients and higher levels of self-reported SB.",
